{"action":"created","issue":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/51245","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/51245/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/51245/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/51245/events","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/51245","id":1887544643,"node_id":"PR_kwDOABkWpM5Z3s3y","number":51245,"title":"Respect pivot strategy (if given) in `cholesky`","user":{"login":"dkarrasch","id":26658441,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI2NjU4NDQx","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/26658441?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch","html_url":"https://github.com/dkarrasch","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":61807486,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw2MTgwNzQ4Ng==","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/labels/linear%20algebra","name":"linear algebra","color":"f2b3db","default":false,"description":"Linear algebra"}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":6,"created_at":"2023-09-08T12:01:42Z","updated_at":"2023-09-25T13:24:37Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"MEMBER","active_lock_reason":null,"draft":false,"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/51245","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/51245","diff_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/51245.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/51245.patch","merged_at":null},"body":"When doing `cholesky(::[Wrapped]SparseMatrixCSC, NoPivot())` the pivoting strategy (the default) was not forwarded to the next call (which used to be `cholesky!`, but now on master has another layer to allow SparseArrays.jl to redirect to SuiteSparse's `cholesky`). Even without the wrapper on `A`, the generic method would take over and direct to the generic, highly unperformant in this case, implementation. With the new redirection layer, this does direct to SparseArrays/SuiteSparse, but because the pivot argument was swallowed in the call, the pivoting strategy is no longer respected: SuiteSparse only knows a fill reducing permutation/pivoting strategy.

Long story short: for generic code that might handle (wrapped) sparse matrices, we do not want to allow calls like `cholesky(A, NoPivot())`, but only `cholesky(A)`.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/51245/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":2,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/51245/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/comments/1733707374","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/51245#issuecomment-1733707374","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/51245","id":1733707374,"node_id":"IC_kwDOABkWpM5nVkZu","user":{"login":"devmotion","id":26102,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI2MTAy","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/26102?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/devmotion","html_url":"https://github.com/devmotion","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/devmotion/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/devmotion/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/devmotion/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/devmotion/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/devmotion/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/devmotion/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/devmotion/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/devmotion/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/devmotion/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2023-09-25T13:24:37Z","updated_at":"2023-09-25T13:24:37Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"ChainRules-based AD of `cholesky` relies on (and only works for) calls with signature `cholesky(::AbstractMatrix, ::NoPivot)` (and `cholesky(::AbstractMatrix, ::Val{false})` on older Julia versions): https://github.com/JuliaDiff/ChainRules.jl/blob/ba52ec89ddd97a07e79cc35a9fa39019915d203b/src/rulesets/LinearAlgebra/factorization.jl#L467 https://github.com/JuliaDiff/ChainRules.jl/blob/ba52ec89ddd97a07e79cc35a9fa39019915d203b/src/rulesets/LinearAlgebra/factorization.jl#L476-L481 https://github.com/JuliaDiff/ChainRules.jl/blob/ba52ec89ddd97a07e79cc35a9fa39019915d203b/src/rulesets/LinearAlgebra/factorization.jl#L491-L496

If I'm not mistaken with this PR, however, it would not be sufficient anymore to catch the two-argument version but one would have to handle both the two- and one-argument version since `cholesky(A)` is directly forwarded to `_cholesky(cholcopy(A))`. This would be fixable by adding `rrule`s for the one-argument version as well (forwarding to the two-argument version) but it seems a bit unfortunate, I have the feeling that the dispatch structure was a bit clearer before when everything went through the two-argument version.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/comments/1733707374/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null}}
